For Benji Daniel and Alex Burger, sailing started as just a weekend activity on the water. Now, they will represent South Africa at the Olympics after eventually being able to attend the qualification event. eNCA’s Justin Ford has the story. Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - Team South Africa could have sailing representation at the Tokyo Olympics. This thanks to Alex Burger and Benji Daniel. The pair qualified in the 49er class at a recent event held in Oman. They are realistic about their chances but have proven they have what it takes to compete with the best. SASCOC will need to confirm Benji and Alex's spots in the Olympic team. Meanwhile, they will prepare to represent their country in Tokyo. * eNCA’s Justin Ford reports.